On Earth Day, I launched my new brand @cozeco , made of timeless essentials that work effortlessly with your everyday style. In case you missed my IG LIVE, watch how I style-out our first collection, ‘BLOOM’, to show you just how easy it is to wear the pieces and seamlessly add them to your existing wardrobe. I love these pieces, and it is so exciting to show you how I personally wear each one. 
 
Follow along to get inspired and #getcoze

#CapitalOnePartner This past year has been all about making the most with what you've got. At the beginning of quarantine, we were cooking like crazy. I thought maybe I'd come out of this year as an incredible home chef. But no. The cooking and cleaning burnout got real real and we started ordering in A LOT to make our days less hectic. The food would arrive and we would sit down to eat with no intention or care about the meal. It made me sad like it was just so anticlimactic and mundane so it was time for me to shake things up a bit. We may be limited on where we can eat dinner, but that doesn’t mean we can’t switch up HOW we do it. With the help of @capitalone, I got to elevate an everyday takeout meal! The little bit of extra effort you put into getting dressed or setting the table or even using your fancy dishes can really give you an elevated feel at home during this difficult time. I got to access and share my creativity, which makes me feel whole.
 
Putting in some work to make yourself happy, will make you a better mom, dad, wife, husband, friend, employee, boss … whatever. Help yourself and then go help someone else. You’ll feel better every time. I can almost promise that! #ElevateTheEveryday Special Thanks to @gigis_la for the delicious food. Y’all MUST go or pick up from there if you’re in LA. XX

Visit WHITNEYPORT.COM and search SKINCARE SUNDAY to shop all of the products I use.

node.text: THEY WERE AMAZING!! We maybe overcooked them a touch, but they were so good. I did it! I'm feeling a lot of shine. Thanks to everyone who watches and leaves comments. You guys are so encouraging, and I love encouragement. Should Timmy and I have our own cooking show? I mean, I think we should. Is there anyone from the Food Network watching and thinking we shouldn't? Because they should be fired immediately. Deborah, you are fired. Sorry. Pack up your sh*t.

node.text: I LOVE Chocolate Soufflé. When you are a person who does not love love a lot of food, the ones you do love, you love hard. I am using the "New York Times Bittersweet Chocolate Soufflé” recipe. Check out next week's to see how it turned out. Let me know in the comments what your favorite dessert is. PEACE!

node.text: My goal today was to beat my rally record of 7.  It's important to set goals! Watch the full video to see if I do it! I am definitely sticking with tennis and am going to play until I can't anymore. Learning how to do all these new things has changed the way I look at my life. The world has so many different things to offer, and I don't have to be an expert at anything to enjoy them. I strongly encourage all of you out there to never stop trying new things.

node.text: I always thought tennis wasn't for me because I didn't grow up playing. But F that! I love it. I'm just starting out and not very good yet, but I'm having so much fun. Unlike yoga, where my mind can wander, I'm always thinking about my form, footwork, or where I want to hit the ball.  By the time my hour is over, I genuinely feel like I have taken a break from the 19 billion things I have to do in a day. Thank Tennis!! What do you guys do to take a mental breather from your days?

I will put you on a poster quick ( Timmy just taught me what that was). 

Are you a “go in the pool” mom or “hang by the chairs” mom?

node.text:
First and foremost, THANK YOU so much for all of your support of my new COZeCO SunDown Collection. 🌅 In fashion, you work so long on something that by the time it’s ready to share you can’t help but feel unsure and anxious about how people may receive it. So, from the bottom of my heart thank you!

This week has been a whirlwind, to say the least. Launching a collection requires SO much micro-managing. It’s one of the most rewarding things in life for me but there are so many moving parts and people involved that feeling frazzled and stressed is inevitable. I don’t mean to be a “Debbie” here at all. Nothing worth having doesn’t come without hard work. I am SO happy and relieved everything is out for you to see, but I am for sure on the verge of burnout. I am making a vow to check in with myself throughout today and tomorrow to make sure my personal and emotional needs are met. I do not want to run myself into the ground. Even as I write this, I can’t stop thinking about everything I have to do today. But I need to take three deep breaths and make sure I hold myself accountable for putting my mental health first. I encourage all of you to take the time to SLOW DOWN. Especially this weekend. Recharge and refresh. Don’t run on fumes. We got this.

OH AND SIDE NOTE! If you follow @cozeco, you’ve probably seen #feelingCOZe. We ask people to share what makes them feel coze and share it in feed and stories! This can range from cuddling on the couch with a blanket to what helps someone feel most comfortable in their own skin. I want YOU involved!! So, I’m leaving you with some work. Post a photo wearing COZeCO tag @cozeco and #getCOZE! My team will reach out to you and see if you want to participate in #feelingCOZE on our channel! YAY! Can’t wait to see you wearing it! xox

Over the past few months on #WITHWHIT, I've tried to make a concerted effort to be as honest and filter-free as possible. It's become one of my mental health practices - speaking my truth and not being afraid of what anyone else is going to think. It’s so essential to check in with yourself mentally and emotionally, even if it’s for a few moments every day, to make sure you are living in alignment with who you really are.

I’ll be honest: last week was a really emotional one. Sonny turned four and I missed my dad so much. In those moments, my grief washed over me and I let myself cry and feel that pain for the first time in a while. Those feelings can be so hard and overwhelming, but they also provide growth and realization. I spent time reflecting and focusing on the steps I needed to take to get to the next moment mindfully.

I also had the idea to compile a “Best of Self-Care with WITH WHIT” featuring some of my past chats on grief and mental health. These include ‘Finding Spirituality & Floating With Grief’, ‘Battling My Harshest Critic, Myself’ & ‘How To Build Habits & Make Them Stick.’ If you’ve listened along to these convos before, I hope they are good reminders – and if you haven’t make sure to check out the full episodes! Link in bio. for this new episode. xx

* App dating
* dating in marriage
* maintaining individuality/identity in a relationship
* the effect that racial biases can have on dating
* the power of curiosity
* the importance of listening when meeting people
 * complementing instead of co-dependency 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Plus she gives tips for setting up your online dating profile and we answer questions you all submitted on my Instagram!
 
This episode is a great one, even if you already have a significant other and are just looking for ways to be a better partner and create a more nurturing relationship. Link is in my bio – hope you all love. Xx
